We're gonna be the richest country in the whole world!

55
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:41,980
再过几周我们就能
So, in the next few weeks we will have

56
00:12:41,990 --> 00:12:45,150
摧毁英国 结束战争
destroyed England and ended the war

57
00:12:45,160 --> 00:12:46,350
既然前线的部队
And since the troops on the front

58
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:49,290
一直高奏凯歌
have been so victorious

59
00:12:49,290 --> 00:12:53,760
我们在后方的人也要尽到自己的责任
it's time that those of us at home do our duty as well

60
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:56,660
元首希望增加产量
The fuhrer wants to increase production

61
00:12:56,670 --> 00:12:58,930
他希望产量在三个月内
He expects productivity to rise by 30 percent

62
00:12:58,940 --> 00:13:01,240
增加三成 再过半年
in three months and to double that

63
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,840
再增加三成
within the next half a year

64
00:13:04,010 --> 00:13:06,540
元首的希望就是我们的命令
The fuhrer's wish is our command

65
00:13:07,740 --> 00:13:09,340
我们现在征求建议
We will now receive any proposals

66
00:13:09,350 --> 00:13:11,350
如何实现这一目标
about how to reach this goal

67
00:13:11,350 --> 00:13:14,620
- 胜利  - 胜利
- Sieg Heil!  - Sieg Heil!

68
00:13:14,620 --> 00:13:18,490
工人们 谁有话要说吗
Workers, does anyone have anything to say?

69
00:13:21,420 --> 00:13:24,590
好的 昆格尔工头
Yes, foreman Quangel?

70
00:13:24,590 --> 00:13:28,000
要提高产量 必须安置
To increase productivity, additional machines

71
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:31,770
更多的机器 还要解雇一些开小差的
must be installed and a few shirkers laid off

72
00:13:31,770 --> 00:13:33,870
你什么意思
What are you talking about?

73
00:13:33,870 --> 00:13:35,540
这些开小差的是谁
Who are those shirkers?

74
00:13:35,540 --> 00:13:37,240
一部分是跟不上工作节奏的
Some can't keep up with the work pace

75
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:39,410
另一部分根本不想跟上
Others don't want to

76
00:13:39,410 --> 00:13:41,540
高谈政治却逃避工作
Talking politics, skipping work

77
00:13:43,410 --> 00:13:45,780
这里有些人对此很擅长
Some men here are good at it Very good

78
00:13:45,780 --> 00:13:48,280
你怎么能这么说 昆格尔
How dare you talk like that, Quangel?

79
00:13:48,290 --> 00:13:50,080
你没有入党
You're not in the party!

80
00:13:50,090 --> 00:13:52,390
你怎么敢污蔑党员
How dare you discredit members of the party!

81
00:13:52,390 --> 00:13:54,990
昆格尔只考虑自己
Quangel only thinks of himself

82
00:13:54,990 --> 00:13:57,230
你有没有为冬季救济金和元首
Do you donate anything to the winter relief fund?

83
00:13:57,230 --> 00:13:58,560
捐赠过什么吗
And to the fuhrer?

84
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:02,300
国家带走了我的独子
Germany has taken my only son

85
00:14:04,070 --> 00:14:07,540
昨天我接到通知他阵亡了
Yesterday, I was informed he died in combat

86
00:14:07,540 --> 00:14:09,600
为了你们 为了元首
For you. For the fuhrer

87
00:14:10,570 --> 00:14:13,310
我来问你 多尔法斯
I ask you, Dolfuss

88
00:14:13,310 --> 00:14:16,610
还有比捐献自己儿子
What more can a man donate

89
00:14:16,610 --> 00:14:18,250
捐的更多的吗
than his child?

90
00:14:29,390 --> 00:14:32,890
安娜 我们还要去征召劳工
Anna! Anna, we have visits to make!

91
00:14:32,900 --> 00:14:35,260
纳粹妇联在等着你
The Nazi women's league is waiting for you!

92
00:14:36,570 --> 00:14:37,600
希特勒万岁 安娜 你去哪儿了
Heil Hitler, Anna! Where were you?

93
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:38,630
- 我们迟到了  - 快点
- We're late!  - Now, come on

94
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:39,930
该走了
It's time to go

95
00:14:39,940 --> 00:14:42,140
- 我们去楼下等你  - 我换衣服 我换衣服
- We'll wait downstairs  - I'll change. I'll change

96
00:14:45,570 --> 00:14:49,140
先是格尔达·克兰施密特夫人
So, first that Frau Gerda Kleinschmidt

97
00:14:49,150 --> 00:14:51,380
然后是一位威尼克夫人
Then there's a Frau else Wernicke

98
00:14:51,380 --> 00:14:52,950
就住在附近 然后是…
who just lives around the corner, and then.

99
00:14:52,950 --> 00:14:55,150
你们听着 克莱尔·格里奇
Ah, listen to this, Claire Gehrich

100
00:14:55,150 --> 00:14:57,490
她是格里奇中校的老婆
Ah, she's the wife of Obersturmbannfuhrer Gehrich

101
00:14:57,490 --> 00:14:59,920
找她的话 需要说的很委婉
You have to be really diplomatic if you visit her

102
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:01,920
- 要不要把她划掉  - 不 我们不能这么做
- Should I cross her out?  - No, no, we can't do that

103
00:15:01,930 --> 00:15:03,420
我们要尽到责任
We all have to do our part

104
00:15:03,430 --> 00:15:05,390
但今天就不去找她了
but, uh, perhaps not today

105
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:07,730
找她那样的人需要有良好的体格
We have to be in good shape for someone like that

106
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:30,220
多么好的房子
What a nice place

107
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:32,790
有什么事吗
What can I do for you?

108
00:15:32,790 --> 00:15:34,920
你的丈夫
Your husband?

109
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:36,660
是的
Yes

110
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:37,830
你丈夫正在波兰作战
Your husband's fighting in Poland

111
00:15:37,830 --> 00:15:39,760
是不是 克兰施密特夫人
isn't he, Frau Kleinschmidt?

112
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:42,130
他每天都为他的民族和祖国
He's risking his life, day after day for his people

113
00:15:42,130 --> 00:15:45,270
冒生命危险 而你却在柏林寻欢作乐
and his fatherland while you are having a good time in Berlin

114
00:15:45,270 --> 00:15:47,040
你不羞愧吗
Aren't you ashamed?

115
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:48,540
可我…
But I.

116
00:15:48,540 --> 00:15:49,640
可是…
But.

117
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:51,670
没人理解
Nobody understands

118
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:55,540
我很担心他
I'm so worried for him

119
00:15:56,380 --> 00:15:58,680
我很担心 可是
I'm so worried, but.

120
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:50,630
都走开
Knock it off!

121
00:16:51,370 --> 00:16:52,800
接着干活
Get back to work

122
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:05,250
别以为这样就不会召你入伍了
Don't think this will save you from the front

123
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:06,880
我不想撒谎
I'm not going to lie

124
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:10,180
我知道你是故意自残
I know you did it on purpose

125
00:17:11,350 --> 00:17:13,020
知道吗
You understand?

126
00:18:35,570 --> 00:18:38,440
如果门铃响了 不要开门
If the doorbell rings, don't open the door

127
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:39,840
谁来都不开门
For anyone

